# üêß Linux Commands Cheat Sheet

> **Your ultimate quick reference for everyday Linux use.**

---

## üìÅ File & Directory Management

| Command  | Description                       |
| -------- | --------------------------------- |
| `ls`     | List files and directories        |
| `cd`     | Change directory                  |
| `pwd`    | Print working directory           |
| `cp`     | Copy files and directories        |
| `mv`     | Move/rename files and directories |
| `rm`     | Remove files                      |
| `rmdir`  | Remove empty directories          |
| `mkdir`  | Make directories                  |
| `find`   | Search for files                  |
| `locate` | Find files by name                |
| `touch`  | Create an empty file              |
| `tree`   | View directory as a tree          |

---

## üìñ File Viewing & Editing

| Command | Description                        |
| ------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `cat`   | Concatenate & display file content |
| `more`  | View file content page by page     |
| `less`  | View file with backward movement   |
| `head`  | View first lines of a file         |
| `tail`  | View last lines of a file          |
| `nano`  | Simple command-line text editor    |
| `vim`   | Advanced text editor               |
| `grep`  | Search for patterns in files       |

---

## üîí Permissions & Ownership

| Command | Description                       |
| ------- | --------------------------------- |
| `chmod` | Change file/directory permissions |
| `chown` | Change file owner and group       |
| `chgrp` | Change group ownership            |

---

## üíª System Information

| Command    | Description                |
| ---------- | -------------------------- |
| `uname -a` | Show system info           |
| `df -h`    | Show disk space usage      |
| `du -sh`   | Show directory/file size   |
| `free -h`  | Show memory usage          |
| `top`      | Show running processes     |
| `htop`     | Interactive process viewer |
| `ps aux`   | Show all running processes |
| `whoami`   | Print current user ID      |
| `uptime`   | Show system uptime         |
| `lscpu`    | CPU architecture info      |

---

## üì¶ Package Management

| Command             | Description                          |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `apt-get update`    | Update package lists (Debian/Ubuntu) |
| `apt-get upgrade`   | Upgrade all packages (Debian/Ubuntu) |
| `yum update`        | Update packages (RHEL/CentOS)        |
| `dnf upgrade`       | Update packages (Fedora/RHEL 8+)     |
| `pacman -Syu`       | Update (Arch Linux)                  |
| `apt install <pkg>` | Install package (Debian/Ubuntu)      |
| `yum install <pkg>` | Install package (RHEL/CentOS)        |
| `dnf install <pkg>` | Install package (Fedora/RHEL 8+)     |
| `pacman -S <pkg>`   | Install package (Arch Linux)         |

---

## üåê Networking

| Command             | Description                      |
| ------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `ping <host>`       | Check network connectivity       |
| `ifconfig`          | Show network interfaces (old)    |
| `ip a`              | Show network interfaces (new)    |
| `iwconfig`          | Show wireless interfaces         |
| `netstat -tulpn`    | Active network connections/ports |
| `ss -tulpn`         | Modern replacement for netstat   |
| `traceroute <host>` | Trace network route              |
| `nslookup <host>`   | Query DNS info                   |
| `dig <host>`        | Query DNS (detailed)             |
| `scp <src> <dst>`   | Secure copy over SSH             |
| `ssh <user>@<host>` | Secure shell connection          |
| `wget <url>`        | Download files from the web      |
| `curl <url>`        | Transfer data to/from server     |

---

## üì¶ Compression & Archiving

| Command                       | Description          |
| ----------------------------- | -------------------- |
| `tar -czvf file.tar.gz <dir>` | Create tarball       |
| `tar -xzvf file.tar.gz`       | Extract tarball      |
| `zip file.zip <file/dir>`     | Compress ZIP archive |
| `unzip file.zip`              | Extract ZIP archive  |
| `gzip <file>`                 | Compress with gzip   |
| `gunzip <file.gz>`            | Decompress gzip      |

---

## üë• User Management

| Command              | Description          |
| -------------------- | -------------------- |
| `adduser <username>` | Add new user         |
| `userdel <username>` | Delete user          |
| `passwd <username>`  | Change user password |
| `su <user>`          | Switch user          |
| `sudo <command>`     | Run as superuser     |

---

## üíΩ Disk & Filesystem

| Command    | Description            |
| ---------- | ---------------------- |
| `fdisk -l` | List disk partitions   |
| `mount`    | Mount filesystem       |
| `umount`   | Unmount filesystem     |
| `lsblk`    | List block devices     |
| `blkid`    | Show block device info |
| `df -Th`   | Disk space by FS type  |

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Process Management

| Command          | Description              |
| ---------------- | ------------------------ |
| `ps`             | Show running processes   |
| `top`            | Real-time process view   |
| `htop`           | Enhanced process monitor |
| `kill <pid>`     | Kill process by PID      |
| `killall <name>` | Kill process by name     |
| `bg`             | Background a job         |
| `fg`             | Foreground a job         |
| `jobs`           | List jobs                |

---

## üöÄ Bonus: Useful Shortcuts

* `Tab` (auto-complete command/filename)
* `Ctrl + C` (terminate running command)
* `Ctrl + D` (logout/exit terminal)
* `Ctrl + Z` (pause process)
* `!!` (repeat last command)

---

> ‚≠ê **Pro tip:** For manual pages about a command, use `man <command>`. Example: `man ls`

---

\:octocat: *Happy hacking!*

